.SH NAME
commitbrief-cache-prune - Drop old/excess cache entries (keep newest N + entries within age window)


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcommitbrief cache prune [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Without flags, defaults to \fB--keep-last 500 --older-than 7d\fR\&. Entries survive only when they sit inside BOTH windows: among the newest keep-last AND not older than older-than. \fB--provider\fR / \fB--model\fR narrow the candidate pool so the rules only touch entries matching those keys; other providers' caches stay untouched.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for prune

.PP
\fB--keep-last\fP=500
	keep only the N newest entries (per the provider/model filter); 0 means keep nothing

.PP
\fB--model\fP=""
	only consider entries written for this model (matched against the model recorded in each entry)

.PP
\fB--older-than\fP="7d"
	delete entries older than this age. Units: d (day), w (week), m (month, 30d), y (year, 365d)

.PP
\fB--provider\fP=""
	only consider entries written for this provider (e.g. anthropic, openai, gemini, ollama)


